### Decisive schema fact
`Enrollment` is UNIQUE on `(schoolId, studentId, termId)` — one row per
student per term → one arm, unambiguous. Mid-term transfers don't create a
second same-term row (they manifest as the NEXT term's row). This collapses
the "which arm for the term" ambiguity (Q1d is N/A) and gives a clean
denominator: the `(termId, classArmId)` enrollment roster.

### Q1 — the ranking spec (12 enumerated cases for the test suite)
- (a) ties → SPARSE "1, 1, 3" (competition ranking; 3-way → 1,1,1,4)
- (b) unscored (no Assessment row) → excluded (no row to rank)
- (c) partial scoring (row exists, partial total) → ranked at the partial
  total (matches slice-2 "partial = partial sum")
- (d) transfer → N/A (one enrollment per term)
- (e) withdrawn → excluded; denominator = Enrollment status=ENROLLED only.
  A non-enrolled student's Assessment row gets subjectPosition/classPosition
  = null (honors the phase-2.md "read the roster live" risk note)
- (f) class position with missing subjects → average over AVAILABLE subjects;
  KNOWN inflation limitation (5/6 subjects ranks by mean(5)); slice-6
  report-card build re-aggregates before release
- (g) single-student arm → position 1
- (h) empty arm → 0 updates, no error
- (i) all-tied → all rank 1
- (j) CRITICAL: subject-narrowed pass must NOT touch classPosition (only a
  full arm pass recomputes overall). Banked Phase-2 lesson: "compute scopes
  must be narrower than write scopes."
- (k) idempotency (re-run → identical positions)
- (l) stable secondary sort by studentId among ties (deterministic test output)

